The returned `sentence` string is the same length as the input `sentence` string.
The returned `sentence` string contains only lowercase letters and spaces.
The returned `sentence` string has the same number of words as the input `sentence` string.
The returned `sentence` string has the same order of words as the input `sentence` string.
The returned `sentence` string has replaced all the successors in the input `sentence` string with the root forming it.
If a successor can be replaced by more than one root, the returned `sentence` string replaces it with the root that has the shortest length.
